description.narrative: (Kosovo): .The READY activity advances the principles of responsible governance by improving legislative and political responsiveness to citizen needs. The principles of political integrity, legislative transparency, government accountability, and citizen inclusion are crucial in any democracy and necessary to help ensure political stability. With FY 2020 funds, USAID will work with Members of Parliament (MPs) and political parties to improve their responsiveness to citizens' needs. MP profiles on the Assembly's website will include data on attendance, public statements, voting patterns, and financial disclosures. The activity will continue to conduct public opinion research to inform the beneficiaries' outreach strategies, caucus legislative plans, party policy development, and gender and youth inclusion strategies. The activity will continue to support the MPs in their efforts to inform the public about legislative business and parliamentary oversight of the executive branch, with the aim of increased opportunities for public input into and scrutiny of legislation. The activity will increase the number of local women and youth leaders and expand their influence and leadership roles in government or within their political party. Through this activity, USAID will strengthen the Assembly and enable its growth as an effective separate branch of government that provides checks and balances. Furthermore, the activity aligns with ICS objective 1.2 and with JRS goal 4.1. This implementing mechanism also supports CAATSA #4; $100,000 are allocated toward interventions that will promote political integrity and legislative transparency through increased engagement between elected officials and citizens........ .. .
